   Apart from the fact that the only newline DMDX ever sees is the one 
that's at the end of a old style parameter line a comment is an item and an 
item at it's barest level is a CR indicator (which in this case is a tilde 
making the item a comment) and a semi-colon that marks the end of the 
item.  It's not at all arbitrary, believe me.

